<subSubSection id="C31265792155FFF8FF221A06FB07FDD9" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22155FFF8FF221A06FB07FDD9" blockId="7.[151,1437,259,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02155FFF8FF221A06FE8FFEF9" bold="true" box="[151,273,259,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02155FFF8FF221A06FE94FEF9" bold="true" box="[151,266,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CF09B172155FFF8FECD1A06FE7AFEFA" box="[376,484,259,286]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="15.5">15.5 mm</quantity>
. Width 
<quantity id="4CF09B172155FFF8FDF61A06FD3FFEFA" box="[579,673,259,286]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="9.6">9.6 mm</quantity>
. Specimen yellowish-brown colored, remnant spots on pronotum indicates a green color when alive or well-preserved dead specimens. Pronotal disc with punctures light brown, except posterior margin that shows black punctures on small dark spots, only part forming irregular lines (
<figureCitation id="13332A772155FFF8FA8C1A4EFA10FE81" box="[1337,1422,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Beneath thorax irregularly punctured with punctures shallow, brown to black on dark spots, some forming sinuous lines (
<figureCitation id="13332A772155FFF8FF691A96FEAFFE49" box="[220,305,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Abdomen shagreen with sparse, shallow, brown punctures on dark spots among brown spots, these dark marks more concentrated on lateral sides of the abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13332A772155FFF8FCE51AB2FC3DFE35" box="[848,931,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Humeral angles projection short, dentiform. Anterior half of the costal margin of corium and hypocostal ridge with punctures on black spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A772155FFF8FB7C1ADEFA80FE11" box="[1225,1310,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Antennae with dark spots on the first three and base of the fourth segment. Legs with dense dark spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A772155FFF8FB6E1AFAFAACFDFD" box="[1243,1330,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Female valvifers 8 strongly projected posteriorly, posterior margins forming sharp spines (
<figureCitation id="13332A772155FFF8FB871926FB13FDD9" box="[1074,1165,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,2002,2026]" captionTargetBox="[210,1365,597,1969]" captionTargetId="figure-181@7.[208,1379,597,1979]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Female genital plates in Ventral view. A: G. longispina sp.n. B: G. brunneotarsata. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500679/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF77667A2155FFF8FF221CD7FB60F80E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500679" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6500679" box="[151,1278,2002,2027]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500679/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" startId="7.[151,250,2002,2026]" targetBox="[210,1365,597,1969]" targetPageId="7">
