<subSubSection id="C3126579215AFFF7FF721B92FBFBFDD9" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215AFFF7FF721B92FDCCFE81" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF721B92FECAFF55" bold="true" box="[199,340,151,177]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF721B92FED3FF55" bold="true" box="[199,333,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head wider than long (1.3 times). Antennae with the fifth segment missing. Thorax: Pronotum wider than long (2.5 times); cicatrices delimited by grooves, not punctuated. Evaporatorium dull, translucid, densely spotted; lateral areas spotted, and half-moon shaped. Metasternal process yellow; anterior bifurcation with arms acuminate; distally with few dark spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FDCF1A06FD4DFEF9" box="[634,723,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Abdomen: connexivum densely and irregularly punctuated; segments III–VI medially with a callus; segment VII with margin and spots dull black. Beneath one trichobothrium in line and the other lateral to spiracles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215AFFF7FF721A6BFBFBFDD9" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF721A6BFE80FE6D" bold="true" box="[199,286,366,393]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FE981A6AFE19FE6D" box="[301,391,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,2002,2026]" captionTargetBox="[210,1365,597,1969]" captionTargetId="figure-181@7.[208,1379,597,1979]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Female genital plates in Ventral view. A: G. longispina sp.n. B: G. brunneotarsata. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500679/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 longer than wide (2 times), sutural border not contiguous; far exceeding valvifers 9, reaching the median line of laterotergites 9. Valvulae 8 medially slightly elevated and somewhat sclerotized, visible between sutural borders of valvifers 8. Valvifers 9 slightly convex, longer than wide (1.3 times), lateral sides partially hidden by valvifers 8. Laterotergites 8 spotted, longer than wide (1.3 times), distal spine well developed slightly exceeding abdominal segment VII. Laterotergites 9 narrow and long, clearly exceeding the band uniting the laterotergites 8, but shorter than laterotergites 8 and level with abdominal segment VII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126579215AFFF7FF721943FAEEFD86" box="[199,1392,582,610]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215AFFF7FF721943FAEEFD86" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,933]" box="[199,1392,582,610]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF721943FED6FD85" bold="true" box="[199,328,582,609]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named for the long spine of the valvifers 8. From the Latin. 
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FC401942FBD9FD84" box="[1013,1095,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Longus</emphasis>
(long) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215AFFF7FB7C1942FA8AFD85" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1816" box="[1225,1300,583,609]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Spinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FB7C1942FA8AFD85" box="[1225,1300,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Spinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(spine).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126579215AFFF7FF72196EFE98FC65" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215AFFF7FF72196EFF46FCDD" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF72196EFEDCFD61" bold="true" box="[199,322,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Comments</emphasis>
. Remnant spots on pronotum indicate that probably pronotal disk has green punctures on green spots that are slightly darker than background like in 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215AFFF7FD5A198AFC20FD4D" authorityName="Correia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2016" box="[751,958,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneotarsata">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FD5A198AFC20FD4D" box="[751,958,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">G. brunneotarsata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215AFFF7FC40198AFB18FD4D" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1013,1158,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fundicava" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FC40198AFB18FD4D" box="[1013,1158,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">G. fundicava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FB38198AFB5BFD4D" bold="true" box="[1165,1221,655,681]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215AFFF7FB38198AFB5BFD4D" box="[1165,1221,655,681]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; among all species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215AFFF7FF0019B6FECBFD29" authorityName="Correia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2016" box="[181,341,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF0019B6FECBFD29" box="[181,341,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Grammedessa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215AFFF7FE2119B6FDB2FD29" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[404,556,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispina" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FE2119B6FDB2FD29" box="[404,556,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">G. longispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FD8719B6FDF4FD29" bold="true" box="[562,618,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215AFFF7FD8719B6FDF4FD29" box="[562,618,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215AFFF7FDCD19B6FC96FD29" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[632,776,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fundicava" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FDCD19B6FC96FD29" box="[632,776,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">G. fundicava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FCBA19B6FCD8FD29" bold="true" box="[783,838,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215AFFF7FCBA19B6FCD8FD29" box="[783,838,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215AFFF7FCE119B6FB80FD29" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[852,1054,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graciligramma" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FCE119B6FB80FD29" box="[852,1054,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">G. graciligramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FB9119B6FBC2FD29" bold="true" box="[1060,1116,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215AFFF7FB9119B6FBC2FD29" box="[1060,1116,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215AFFF7FB2C19B6FAC3FD29" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1177,1373,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stichtocephala" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FB2C19B6FAC3FD29" box="[1177,1373,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">G. stichtocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FAD119B6FA02FD29" bold="true" box="[1380,1436,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215AFFF7FAD119B6FA02FD29" box="[1380,1436,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
share a posterior stripe of black punctures on the pronotum. But only the first three show black spots on legs. 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215AFFF7FA3419D2FE93FCF1" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispina" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FA3419D2FE93FCF1" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">G. longispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FEA319FEFED0FCF1" bold="true" box="[278,334,763,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215AFFF7FEA319FEFED0FCF1" box="[278,334,763,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is separated from the other two species by the ventral side of the body with dark punctures and spots.
</paragraph>
